    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1887-10-07T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1887-10-07T00:00:00-05:00" n="68" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d68">
                <head>No. 68.<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Bayard</persName>
                            to Mr. <persName type="to">Hall</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department
                                    of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1887-10-07">
                            <hi rend="italic">October</hi> 7,
                            1887</date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 505.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have received your telegram of the 30th
                        ultimo, saying that the Nicaraguan Congress had rejected the boundary
                        convention with Costa Rica.</p>
                <pb facs="0214" n="80" xml:id="pg_80"/>
                <p>Similar information had already been received here through the diplomatic
                        representatives of those Governments at this capital; and in a note to the
                        Costa Rican minister, after acknowledging his upon that subject, I have
                        said, “that I thus learn with regret that the expected course of direct
                        settlement of the questions between two countries to which the United States
                        are equally friendly is interrupted.”</p>
                <p>I am, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">T. F.
                            Bayard.</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
